                <h1>Wallpapering Textured Walls: Tips & Techniques</h1>
                <p>Yes, you can wallpaper textured walls, but preparation is key. Smooth out the surface as much as possible to ensure proper adhesion. Use a thick wallpaper or a lining paper to help conceal the texture, which will result in a more polished finish. Consider using paste-the-wall wallpaper for easier application and adjustments.</p>
